# CVE-2025-15558 — HIGH severity in github.com/docker/cli embedded in the Trivy binary.
# This is a Windows-only vulnerability (named pipe path traversal).
# Not applicable to Linux containers.
CVE-2025-15558

# CVE-2026-33186 — CRITICAL severity in google.golang.org/grpc embedded in the Trivy binary.
# gRPC-Go authorization bypass via missing leading slash in :path pseudo-header.
# Trivy runs as a local CLI scanner and does not expose a gRPC endpoint. Not exploitable.
# Fixed in gRPC-Go v1.79.3; Trivy v0.69.3 ships v1.78.0. Awaiting upstream release.
CVE-2026-33186

# CVE-2026-25679 — HIGH severity in Go stdlib net/url embedded in the Trivy binary.
# Incorrect parsing of IPv6 host literals. Trivy only connects to known DB mirrors.
# Fixed in Go v1.25.8 / v1.26.1; Trivy v0.69.3 is built with Go v1.25.7. Awaiting upstream release.
CVE-2026-25679

# CVE-2026-27142 — MEDIUM severity in Go stdlib html/template embedded in the Trivy binary.
# XSS via unescaped URLs in meta content attributes. Trivy does not render HTML templates.
# Fixed in Go v1.25.8 / v1.26.1; Trivy v0.69.3 is built with Go v1.25.7. Awaiting upstream release.
CVE-2026-27142

# CVE-2026-27139 — LOW severity in Go stdlib os embedded in the Trivy binary.
# FileInfo can escape from a Root via race condition. Trivy does not use os.Root.
# Fixed in Go v1.25.8 / v1.26.1; Trivy v0.69.3 is built with Go v1.25.7. Awaiting upstream release.
CVE-2026-27139
